Aviwe Klaas, 24 

What is Youth Day about?
To me Youth Day commemorates the youth of 1976, and what happened to the youth of 1976.
What does Youth Day mean to you?
It means freedom.
What strides have been made by the youth, since 1976?
Recently, we have seen youth take part in the #FeesMustFall movement for free education and debate about the NSFAS(National Students Financial Aid Scheme) and so forth. Everything that has happened is because of the freedom that we, as students and the youth of today, have.
How can we work together to better assist the youth of today in making decisions?
People, not only those in the cities, should be made aware of the opportunities they have. People should be informed of the choices they have currently, because our future has been fought for.
What lessons can our youth learn from the youth of 1976?
To work collaboratively, because the youth of 1976 were in partnership. Now when people were fighting for their rights, for example during the #FeesMustFall campaign, others were relaxing at home. If we work collaboratively we can achieve a lot in life.







