Mdodana Weziwe, 26


What is Youth Day about?
Youth Day to me is freedom day to the youth of South Africa.

What does Youth Day mean to you?
It means I’m free to get education, I’m free to get everything in South Africa.

What strides have been made by the youth, since 1976?
Free education. We are well educated now, because of the youth of 1976. We have bursaries, we have access to everything because of that youth.

What are the challenges facing the youth today?
Unemployment. Even if they are educated, they don’t get employment and [endure] poverty.

How can we work together to better assist the youth of today in making better decisions?
To educate them, give them the opportunities. Education is the key to everything.

What lessons can the youth of 2018 learn from the youth of 1976?
What they can learn is to fight for what we want; you have to fight for it.







